{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775886996505,"sessionID":"ses_284e4764cffe5o2r3TS0MKiDro","part":{"id":"prt_d7b1c7ae2001G4bkFNTm1LBVsl","messageID":"msg_d7b1c728f001dfgdy2QxFfeirO","sessionID":"ses_284e4764cffe5o2r3TS0MKiDro","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_7c7e9a6e0c604dea9a89f16e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-037 — PCAP 分析器示例应用 Tasks\n\n**Module:** example  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n**Stage:** Not started\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: Project Setup\n\n- [ ] **T1.1** Create example directory structure\n  - Directory: `sdk-python/examples/pcap_analyzer/`\n  - Subdirectory: `sdk-python/examples/pcap_analyzer/test_pcaps/`\n  - Verify: `ls -la sdk-python/examples/pcap_analyzer/` shows directories\n\n- [ ] **T1.2** Create requirements.txt with dependencies\n  - File: `sdk-python/examples/pcap_analyzer/requirements.txt`\n  - Content: `scapy>=2.5.0`\n  - Verify: `cat requirements.txt` shows scapy dependency\n\n- [ ] **T1.3** Create README.md with usage instructions\n  - File: `sdk-python/examples/pcap_analyzer/README.md`\n  - Sections: Features, Prerequisites, Installation, Usage, Example Output, How It Works, Error Handling, Troubleshooting\n  - Verify: File exists with complete documentation\n\n---\n\n## Phase 2: Sample PCAP Generation\n\n- [ ] **T2.1** Create sample_pcap.py script\n  - File: `sdk-python/examples/pcap_analyzer/sample_pcap.py`\n  - Imports: scapy modules (Ether, IP, TCP, UDP, DNS, DNSQR, Raw, wrpcap)\n  - Verify: File exists with correct imports\n\n- [ ] **T2.2** Implement HTTP traffic PCAP generator\n  - Function: `create_basic_http_pcap(output_path)`\n  - Packets: HTTP GET request + HTTP response\n  - Output: `test_pcaps/basic_http.pcap`\n  - Verify: `python sample_pcap.py` generates file > 0 bytes\n\n- [ ] **T2.3** Implement DNS queries PCAP generator\n  - Function: `create_dns_queries_pcap(output_path)`\n  - Packets: DNS queries (example.com, google.com) + responses\n  - Output: `test_pcaps/dns_queries.pcap`\n  - Verify: Generated PCAP contains DNS layers\n\n- [ ] **T2.4** Test sample generation\n  - Command: `cd sdk-python/examples/pcap_analyzer && python sample_pcap.py`\n  - Verify: Both `basic_http.pcap` and `dns_queries.pcap` exist\n  - Verify: Files can be read by wireshark/tcpdump\n\n---\n\n## Phase 3: PCAP Analyzer Core Implementation\n\n- [ ] **T3.1** Create pcap_analyzer.py main script\n  - File: `sdk-python/examples/pcap_analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py`\n  - Imports: os, sys, json, logging, pathlib, typing, agentcube.CodeInterpreterClient\n  - Verify: File exists with correct structure\n\n- [ ] **T3.2** Implement PcapAnalyzer class initialization\n  - Class: `PcapAnalyzer`\n  - Method: `__init__(router_url, workload_manager_url, auth_token, verbose)`\n  - Initialize: `CodeInterpreterClient(name=\"pcap-analyzer\")`\n  - Set paths: `remote_pcap_dir`, `remote_results_dir`, `remote_analyzer_script`\n  - Verify: Class can be instantiated\n\n- [ ] **T3.3** Implement setup_environment method\n  - Method: `setup_environment()`\n  - Commands: `mkdir -p` for directories, `pip install scapy --quiet`\n  - Verify: Sandbox directories created and scapy installed\n\n- [ ] **T3.4** Implement upload_pcap method\n  - Method: `upload_pcap(local_path) -> str`\n  - Validation: Check file exists\n  - Upload: `client.upload_file(local_path, remote_path)`\n  - Verify: `client.list_files()` shows uploaded file\n\n- [ ] **T3.5** Implement create_analyzer_script method\n  - Method: `create_analyzer_script()`\n  - Script content: `analyze_pcap(pcap_path)` function\n  - Features: Protocol detection (TCP/UDP/OTHER), IP extraction, port extraction, DNS query extraction\n  - Write: `client.write_file(script_content, remote_analyzer_script)`\n  - Verify: Script exists in sandbox\n\n- [ ] **T3.6** Implement analyze_pcap method\n  - Method: `analyze_pcap(remote_pcap_path) -> Dict[str, Any]`\n  - Execute: `client.run_code()` with analyzer script\n  - Download: `client.download_file(output_path, local_path)`\n  - Return: Parsed JSON results\n  - Error handling: CommandExecutionError, DataPlaneError\n  - Verify: Returns correct analysis results\n\n- [ ] **T3.7** Implement close method\n  - Method: `close()`\n  - Action: `client.stop()`\n  - Verify: Session properly cleaned up\n\n---\n\n## Phase 4: CLI & Entry Point\n\n- [ ] **T4.1** Implement command-line argument parsing\n  - Function: `main()`\n  - Arguments: `pcap_file` (positional), `--router-url`, `--workload-manager-url`, `--auth-token`, `-v/--verbose`, `--generate-samples`\n  - Epilog: Usage examples\n  - Verify: `python pcap_analyzer.py --help` shows all arguments\n\n- [ ] **T4.2** Implement main execution flow\n  - Flow: Check generate-samples → Validate file → Initialize analyzer → Setup → Create script → Upload → Analyze → Print results\n  - Output: JSON formatted results\n  - Verify: Complete flow executes without errors\n\n- [ ] **T4.3** Implement error handling\n  - Exceptions: FileNotFoundError, CommandExecutionError, DataPlaneError, generic Exception\n  - Finally block: Call `analyzer.close()`\n  - Verify: Errors are caught and logged appropriately\n\n---\n\n## Phase 5: Testing & Validation\n\n- [ ] **T5.1** Test sample generation\n  - Command: `python sample_pcap.py`\n  - Verify: Two PCAP files created in test_pcaps/\n  - Verify: Files are valid PCAP format\n\n- [ ] **T5.2** Test basic HTTP PCAP analysis\n  - Command: `python pcap_analyzer.py test_pcaps/basic_http.pcap`\n  - Verify: Output contains `total_packets: 2`\n  - Verify: Output contains `protocols: {TCP: 2}`\n  - Verify: Output contains IP addresses\n\n- [ ] **T5.3** Test DNS PCAP analysis\n  - Command: `python pcap_analyzer.py test_pcaps/dns_queries.pcap`\n  - Verify: Output contains `protocols: {UDP: ...}`\n  - Verify: Output contains `dns_queries: [\"example.com\", \"google.com\"]`\n\n- [ ] **T5.4** Test error handling - missing file\n  - Command: `python pcap_analyzer.py nonexistent.pcap`\n  - Verify: FileNotFoundError is raised a